            <thetext>One critical aspect of the virtual widgets is when/how to update which parts of the widgets.

It is critical to have a consistent policy of how things get updated.

Events, which could trigger an update:

 1. the axis configuration changes
 2. the viewport changes by
    - pane resize
    - pane scrolling
 3. the data of a specific layer is changed (e.g. the row color in a Row layer)
  
 The ILayer interface right now only provides methods to handle the first two cases. Some layers provide basic functionality for case 3 by implementing &quot;syncWidget&quot;. This is however not very intuitive and not enforced in all layers.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
